post.description:
Adds one or more Clients to an existing Home.

The body of the request should be formatted as an array of hashes/objects, with each hash containing a `type` key and an `id` key. See the below example:
```
{
  "data": [
    { "type": "clients", "id": "9e3c1b31-89fd-46f0-99e0-33f8f920e7a0" },
    { "type": "clients", "id": "24628cab-9612-4e8b-966b-f53e16d33be9" }
  ]
}
```

delete.description:
Removes one or more Clients from an existing Home. The Client and the Home will still exist, but the relationship will be destroyed.

The body of the request should be formatted as an array of hashes/objects, with each hash containing a `type` key and an `id` key. See the below example:
```
{
  "data": [
    { "type": "clients", "id": "7bbb0383-39dd-40ef-b8d1-761c47cd4c65" },
    { "type": "clients", "id": "3db8f079-74ca-4b05-b0c4-2e8c63c20ca4" }
  ]
}
```
